{"word":"εὐρύς","slug":"εὐρύς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐρύς</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>wide, broad</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>far-reaching, far-spread</i>, <el>κλέος εὐρύ</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>ἐλπίδες</el> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> the <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <el>εὐρύ</el> is mostly used, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}